node.text:
"Zadowolenie i spokój pojawiają się, gdy płomień ducha nie chwieje się na wietrze pragnień" - B.K.S. Iyengar

Santosa to jedna z Nijam - praktyka zadowolenia, z tego co mamy, kim jesteśmy, co nam przynosi życie, a także z tego na co w danym momencie pozwala nam nasze ciało w praktyce jogi. 
Niezadowolenie rodzi chciwość i zazdrość. Santosa rodzi stan umysłu, który ułatwia skupienie i jest źródłem szczęścia. Praktyka trudniejsza niż zrobienie takiej #pozycjakruka Trzeba się cały czas pilnować ;) Photo credit @natalkamay

Nyttårs-forsett=nyttårs\2=nytt og års. Nytt år, Ny dag, nytt minutt. Forandring skjer HEEEELEEEE tiden. Ikke la ett nyttårsforsett make you or brake you. Finn på noe nytt en annen dag. Vær spontan og leken med ideene og målene du setter for din spirituelle utvikling. .
Denne måneden i klassene mine vil vi se nærmere på «squat’n crow» (squat posisjon og armbalansen crow) .
squat’n crow er del av dagens «nyttårsforsett» det å finne på et nytt catchy ord😂😂😂

node.text:
Crow, or Bakasana, is one of the first hand balancing postures I practiced when I started yoga. When I was younger, it came easily. I had a strong core (can we say 6 pack - say whaaaaaat 😳). However, that changed after I got pregnant and had my son 👶
.
I ended up having an emergency C-Section and recovery has taken me, quite literally, years. My muscles were totally shot and it took me a year before I even felt comfortable doing consecutive crunches. Now, I feel much stronger and as I was scrolling through photos I found my crow (or baby crow some would say) from a year ago, and my crow pose from last month. My son is 5 - and that’s how long it has taken me. Some recoveries don’t take that long, but keep in mind with resolutions sometimes it doesn’t take a week, month, or even year. This is a continual practice and a huge shoutout to those who have undergone surgery, injury, childbirth, or weight fluctuations. I see you, I hear you, and we are on this journey together ✌🏻
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
. .
